  <original-body>calling `inspect` for a duration of `0.seconds` returns an empty string.  This surprised me.  I'd have expected one of the following:

* `'0 seconds'` (or minutes/hours/years)
* `'0'`

The attached patch (against master) makes `0.seconds.inspect` return `&quot;0 seconds&quot;`</original-body>
